(firstQuint)Description of the Appearance of Brown Fat in Scanner.

 Brown fat is metabolically active adipose tissue.

 It can be responsible in PET-CT of a fixation of 18-FDG and a look of pseudo-infiltration of fat.

 These aspects can be sources of false positives.

 The objective here is to gain a better knowledge of the scanner in areas of brown fat.

